{
  "_comment": [
    "===================================================================================",
    "Kuber v1.7.3 - users.json Sample Configuration",
    "===================================================================================",
    "",
    "This file defines user accounts for Kuber cache authentication and authorization.",
    "",
    "IMPORTANT NOTES:",
    "  - The 'admin' user is RESERVED and cannot be deleted or have its role removed",
    "  - When either users.json OR roles.json changes, BOTH files are reloaded",
    "  - Changes take effect within 30 seconds (auto-reload) or immediately via Admin UI",
    "  - If this file is missing, a default with only 'admin' user is created",
    "",
    "FIELD DESCRIPTIONS:",
    "  userId      - Unique login identifier (required, alphanumeric/underscore/hyphen)",
    "  password    - Authentication password (required, stored in cleartext)",
    "  fullName    - Display name shown in UI (required)",
    "  email       - Email address (optional)",
    "  roles       - Array of role names granting permissions (required, see roles.json)",
    "  enabled     - Account is active and can log in (default: true)",
    "  locked      - Account is locked due to failed logins (default: false)",
    "  systemUser  - System account that cannot be deleted (default: false)",
    "  createdAt   - ISO timestamp of account creation (auto-set)",
    "  createdBy   - User who created this account (auto-set)",
    "",
    "ROLE ASSIGNMENT EXAMPLES:",
    "  [\"admin\"]                           - Full system access to all regions",
    "  [\"default_readonly\"]                - Read-only access to 'default' region",
    "  [\"default_full\"]                    - Full access to 'default' region",
    "  [\"orders_readonly\", \"products_full\"]- Read orders, full access to products",
    "",
    "SECURITY RECOMMENDATIONS:",
    "  - Change default admin password immediately",
    "  - Use strong passwords (8+ chars, mixed case, numbers, symbols)",
    "  - Apply principle of least privilege (minimal required roles)",
    "  - Regularly audit user accounts and role assignments",
    "==================================================================================="
  ],
